Flash: Go to the raspberry Pi Official website 
Go to the Raspberry Pi Imager page 
Pick your computer OS (Windows, MacOS, Ubuntu and even Terminal) 
Download 
Open the Downloaded file and accept all the terms 
Raspberry pi Imager should now be downloaded and available to use 
Click on it, and accept that it should make modifications on your computer 
Insert an SD card using an adapter or by directly inserting it to your computer 
First: Pick your raspberry pi device 
10- Second: Pick your OS system (64-bit, 32-bit, legacy 32-bit, etc...). We took the Legacy 32-bit since it comes with the picamera Library 
 Thirdly: pick your SD card storage 
